Good — the annotation axiom approach catches all PR cases. Now let me check 
  the URL-style xrefs more carefully:

Bash: Find URL-style UniProt xrefs on measurement terms
$ cd /home/runner/work/efo/efo/src/ontology && ../../bin/robot query --use-
  graphs true --catalog catalog-v001.xml --input efo-edit.owl --query         
  /dev/stdin /dev/stdout <<'EOF'                                              
    prefix oio: <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#>               
    prefix owl: <http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#>                              
    prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>                      
    prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>                 
    prefix obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>                             
                                                                              
    # Check URL-style UniProt xrefs on measurement terms                      
    SELECT ?term ?term_label ?xref                                            
    WHERE {                                                                   
      ?term rdf:type owl:Class ;                                              
        rdfs:subClassOf+ <http://www.ebi.ac.uk/efo/EFO_0001444> ;             
        oio:hasDbXref ?xref .                                                 
      FILTER(isIRI(?term))                                                    
      FILTER(REGEX(?xref, "^https?://.*uniprot.org/(uniprot|uniprotkb)/[A-Z0- 
  9]", "i"))                                                                  
      OPTIONAL { ?term rdfs:label ?term_label . }                             
    }                                                                         
    ORDER BY ?xref                                                            
