## Summary                                                                  
                                                                              
  Addressed @jamesamcl's request to verify exhaustive coverage of all UniProt 
  ID permutations. After a systematic audit of the ontology, I found one gap: 
  2 measurement terms with URL-style UniProt xrefs                            
  (https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/*/entry) that were not being captured.   
                                                                              
  **Changes in 680bedc:**                                                     
                                                                              
  • Added a new UNION branch to the SPARQL query for URL-style UniProt xrefs, 
  with REGEX extraction and normalization to uniprot: prefix                  
  • This captures EFO_0004614 (apolipoprotein A 1 measurement → P02647) and   
  EFO_0020072 (soluble CD163 measurement → Q86VB7)                            
  • Total: 3,028 mappings (2,975 EFO + 53 OBA)                                
                                                                              
  The query now covers 5 exhaustive paths across all verified prefix formats.

